	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Johannesburg - A 32-year-old man was airlifted to hospital after he fell three floors at a construction site in Randpark Ridge, Johannesburg on Thursday afternoon, paramedics said. Netcare911 spokesperson Nick Dollman said the man was in a serious condition due to several serious fractures that he had sustained. Dollman said he was stabilised by ground crews and medication had been administered to reduce his pain. He was then airlifted to a specialised trauma unit in Johannesburg.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  